race.description: Carpet Call Qtis Three-Year-Old Maiden Plate
race.comment: READY FOR AIMEE (14) is back from a 143-day spell. Has only raced once, leading for home over this distance at Doomben only to be swamped close to home. Trialling in good style and this looks a nice race to launch the second campaign. LYNEHAM (15) has only raced once and it was in the same Doomben maiden as the top pick. Settled midfield that day and worked home well to be beaten just 1.7 lengths. Draws a very wide gate but with any luck can feature in the finish. Locally trained CRASH THE PARTY (9) is back from an 18-week lay-off. Impressed in the maiden prep with a couple of minor placings before failing in Autumn Boy's Tatts Stakes. Big recent trial winner who looks ready for a positive return. YOUMEANDDUPRE (7) has not raced since a close fourth to the smart Call Da Vinci over 1350m at Ipswich in May. Ready to run well on the back of two recent trial wins. EGYPTIAN GODDESS (10) is rarely far away and should be considered for exotics.
